sql:
SELECT version_number, release_date
FROM component_versions
WHERE version_id = 0;

SELECT components.description, component_demand_forecasts.forecast_date, component_demand_forecasts.quantity_forecasted
FROM component_demand_forecasts
JOIN components ON component_demand_forecasts.component_id = components.component_id;

SELECT component_id, lead_time_days
FROM supplier_lead_times
WHERE lead_time_days > 10;

external_knowledge:
- 'slow-to-procure' refers to components with a lead time greater than 30 days;
- 'haven't been ordered recently' implies no orders have been placed in the last 30 days;
- 'stock left' refers to the quantity on hand in the inventory.

sql:
SELECT component_id, description, quantity_per_board
FROM components
WHERE component_id > 5 AND manufacturer_id = 1;

SELECT supplier_id, AVG(lead_time_days) AS average_lead_time
FROM supplier_lead_times
GROUP BY supplier_id;

external_knowledge:
- "shining the brightest" metaphorically refers to the component with the highest average forecasted quantity; 
- "short-term forecast horizon" refers to the 'short-term' type of forecast;
- "average quantity forecasted of at least 10 units" refers to the condition that the sum of `quantity_forecasted` must be 10 or more, and the highest average is to be found.
